<script>
function openNav() {
    document.getElementById("mySidenav").style.display = "block";
	 document.getElementById("mySidenav").style.width = "250px";
    document.getElementById("main").style.marginLeft = "250px";
}

function closeNav() {
    document.getElementById("mySidenav").style.display = "none";
	document.getElementById("mySidenav").style.width = "0";
    document.getElementById("main").style.marginLeft= "0";
}
</script>
<div align="left" id="main">
<h1>Breakthrough</h1>
<p style="text-align:left;">
Bismuth Borate glass has been tested for radiation protection and strength. Increasing the ratio of bismuth gives it more radiation protection while increasing the ratio of borate makes it stronger. The R value is the ratio of bismuth to borate. As you can see as the R value increases so does the density (good for radiation protection) and the molar volume (good for rigidity) mostly following a logarithmic curve.
</p>
